---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { AUTHOR } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Who is behind The Anomaly Desk and the Is Neo Human? investigation into The Matrix."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'About', path: '/about' },
  ]}
>
  <div class="container">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>The Anomaly Desk</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      A small, obsessive film-analysis project dedicated to a single question
      the Wachowskis never directly answered: <em>is Neo actually human?</em>
    </p>

    <p>
      We re-watch the trilogy (plus <em>Matrix Resurrections</em>) frame by
      frame, cross-reference the dialogue, and build the most rigorous,
      good-faith version of a theory most fans dismiss without examining: that
      Neo may be a machine-made construct rather than a freed human.
    </p>

    <h2>Our standard</h2>
    <p>
      Every claim on this site is tied to something that actually happens in
      the films. We separate <strong>what is canon</strong> (the real-world
      Sentinel scene, the Architect's dialogue, Neo's resurrection) from
      <strong>what is interpretation</strong>. We argue a position, but we show
      our work and present the counter-evidence honestly.
    </p>

    <h2>Not affiliated</h2>
    <p>
      {AUTHOR} is an independent fan project. We are not affiliated with Warner
      Bros., Village Roadshow Pictures, or the creators of The Matrix. All film
      references are made for purposes of criticism and commentary.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-top:28px">
      <a class="cta" href="/evidence">Start with the evidence →</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
